        <updateDate>2019-08-26T18:37:33Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Rare disease Advancement, Research, and Education Act of 2018 or the RARE Act of 2018</strong></p> <p>This bill reauthorizes through FY2023 the Office of Rare Diseases in the National Institutes of Health.</p> <p>The bill requires (1) the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention to expand infrastructure and activities to track the epidemiology of rare diseases and conditions and to incorporate&nbsp;this information into a National Rare Disease or Condition Surveillance System, and (2) the Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality to expand its activities to increase providers' awareness of rare diseases and conditions.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
